                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/jd/Subjects/Immigration/midtspalte/Fact-sheet-White-paper-on-Norwegian-refugee-and-migration-policy-in-a-European-perspective.html?id=600197" title="">
                        Fact sheet: White paper on Norwegian refugee and migration policy in a European perspective
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Editorial article, Ministry of Justice and the Police, 13.04.2010]</p>
                <p>This fact sheet presents the content of the white paper on Norwegian refugee and migration policy in a European perspective and the Government’s 22 main priorities in the field of refugees and migration in the time ahead.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp1591643909_wp1630463120_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl00_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/bld/aktuelt/nyheter/2010/International-Migration-2008-2009.html?id=593998" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/BLD/Ingresssbilder/Verden_100x75.gif" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/bld/aktuelt/nyheter/2010/International-Migration-2008-2009.html?id=593998" title="">
                        International Migration 2008-2009
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[News story, Ministry of Children, Equality and Social Inclusion, 24.02.2010]</p>
                <p>Annually Norway sends a report to the OECD – Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development – as a contribution to the common reporting system on migration for the OECD countries, called SOPEMI. The recent report for Norway covers 2008 and to some extent 2009.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp1591643909_wp1630463120_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl01_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/jd/Documents-and-publications/Reports/Reports/2009/International-Migration-2008-20091.html?id=602249" title="">
                        International Migration 2008-2009
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Report, Ministry of Justice and the Police, 22.12.2009]</p>
                <p>Annually Norway sends a report to the OECD – Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development – as a contribution to the common reporting system on migration for the OECD countries, called SOPEMI. The recent report for Norway covers 2008 and to some extent 2009.</p>
                
                
